Mechanics page to edit

New Game+[edit]

Once you've completed the Symphony, you can start New Game+. New Game+ is required for the completion of certain sub-events and item collection as well as getting all of the Symphony characters.

The story is divided into 3 branches

Kid

Harle

Neither (Must have completed other branches and Chapter 25)

You will need to complete Kid's route twice to complete one of the sub-events. Blue Chest in Another World can be open only once and the contents will not respawn upon New Game+

"Field Effect" Battle Mechanics[edit]

The "Field Effect" can be seen in the top left corner in battle at all Another World locations. Each time an enemy or ally perform an elemental attack, a color corresponding to the element will light up on the "Field Effect" Field effect stack up to 3 actions, after which they will be overwritten in order of the oldest action. Null element attacks and non attack moves do not affect "Field Effects"

"Field Effects" gives 70% elemental damage boost for all allies and enemies for each ring lighted with a respective element (max 210% boost for all three rings). The rings are filled starting from the inner circle, and the rings are shifted outwards for each use of an element.

Difficulty Setting[edit]

The difficulty of the symphony can be toggled at any time. The difficulty affects the strength and health of mobs, horrors, and bosses. At the highest difficulty, mobs can have up to 500,000 HP and horrors up to 30 million, with priority moves.

Once you've beaten the final boss, you'll also be given rewards tied to the difficulties lower than the one you've selected; e.g. beating the Symphony on Veteran will also yield rewards given for Beginner and Standard difficulty.

Difficulty Level Beginner 30 Standard 60 Veteran 70 Expert 80 Master 110

Skip[edit]

After starting New Game+, the Skip feature will be unlocked. The Skip feature can't be used under the following conditions:

When there are unread event scenes

Before the prologue starts, and when skip destination is the ending

When there is an event scene that has branching decision

Summary[edit]

The beginning, since lost to oblivion...

A memory now nothing but a faded echo.

Time stopped for me then.

A soul with no place, I became a petal on the wind.

Until suddenly, a clock long since broken

carefully and quietly began to move...

And with it, something started anew in you.

Our future, our tomorrow...

Beckoned forth...

By familiar voices from beyond the dark...

Dreamslip Tower of Time Clock Puzzle[edit]

Clock starts at 6.15. Red cards turn the minute hand clockwise, blue cards turn hour hand anti-clockwise. Reaching 12 with minute hand turns hour hand forward by 1 hour. Solution to unlock rooms as follows. After collecting all cards, other rooms are skippable.

Insert Red 20 to open 7 o'clock (Red 20)

Insert Blue 4 to open 2 o'clock (Red 20, Blue 4)

Insert Red 30 to open 1 o'clock (Red 20, Red 30, Blue 4)

Insert Red 15 to open 4 o'clock (Red 15, Red 20, Red 30, Blue 4)

Remove Red 30 to open 10 o'clock (Red 15, Red 20, Blue 4)

Insert Blue 6 to open 8 o'clock (Red 15, Red 20, Blue 4, Blue 6)

Insert Blue 3 to open 5 o'clock (Red 15, Red 20, Blue 3, Blue 4, Blue 6) -- blue chest+blueprint

==All cards collected.==

Remove Blue 6 to open 11 o'clock (Red 15, Red 20, Blue 3, Blue 4) -- Shiny Alloy

Remove Red 15, Red 20, Blue 4 to open 3 o'clock (Blue 3) -- blue chest

Insert Red 30, Blue 6 to open 9 o'clock (Red 30, Blue 3, Blue 6) -- blue chest

Remove all and insert Red 15 to open 6 o'clock (Red 15) -- element

Insert Red 30, Blue 3, Blue 4 to open 12 o'clock (Red 15, Red 30, Blue 3, Blue 4) -- Exit

Bonus page to edit

Night Travel[edit]

In New Game+, you will have Freight Carrier Pass in your key item inventory from the first playthrough, and after Chapter 1 but prior to starting Chapter 2, you are able to leave Unigalna while it is night. This is the only to access Another Baruoki and Another Rinde at night.

Another Spacetime Rift[edit]

The sparkling bucket in Another Spacetime Rift may be selected in order to refight the story bosses at selected difficulty.

There is a goblin at the back which requests you to circle him clockwise (i.e. down-left-up-right) three times consecutively. This allows fighting of 2 hidden bosses, Lynx and Dragon God available at Another Spacetime Rift after completing Complex Dream. There will be a jingle if one circle is completed. If you are having trouble completing a circle, stop moving left/right just before going up/down so the character does not move out of the circle while going up or down.

Unigalna Hidden Stuff[edit]

Keep tapping the large barrel in the Tavern (left side) for 1 High Class Scroll. Repeat for a "Castle Wall Key" Key Item.

Next, tap on the wooden doors next to both gates in Unigalna to enter corridors leading to doors that can be unlocked with the Castle Wall Key. 1 High Class Scroll and 3 Guiding Lights (Ax).

Head two houses right from the Inn. Tap on the bed to reveal a hidden staircase leading down to a Scarlet Meteorite.

Elements page to edit

Elements[edit]

In 2.10.200 version of game, the characters that become your allies in Symphony: Complex Dream don't have any style but instead can wear special equipment called Elements. The number of Elements a character can be equipped with increases with their level, maxing out at four.

Serge has a unique passive that allows him to change all of his ability board skills to the element equipped in his first slot.

Harle is the only character capable of getting to Power Level 12 which allows for her skills to gain a higher percentage for stack effects.

A strategy that takes advantage of Power Level 12 is to have Harle use Lunar Protection and Anti-Element (E) with max Power Level which would allow for a 100% type resistance. See Harle: Strategy for more details

How to collect[edit]

Elements drop from golden chests that are refreshed on each New Game+ of the collab. Element type-skill is fixed in same chest. Elemental types are randomized each time.
